        <profileDesc>
            <creation/>
            <abstract>
                <p>The miracle of a Christian whose hands and feet withered because of an act of perjury is cured by St Michael. Seeing 
                    this, a Jew was converted to Christianity. This miracle is thematically similar to <ref target="LIT1295Dersan#MiracleFreed"/>. It is transmitted in the section for Miyāzyā 
                    in most manuscripts and in the section for Ṭǝrr in <ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BAVet121">Vatican City, Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana, Aeth. 121</ref></p>
            </abstract>
